      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/23/3/110/9",
      "text": [
        " سَمِعْتُ أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ ع یَقُولُ لَا خَیْرَ فِی وَلَدِ الزِّنَاءِ وَ لَا فِی بَشَرِهِ وَ لَا فِی شَعْرِهِ وَ لَا فِی لَحْمِهِ وَ لَا فِی دَمِهِ وَ لَا فِی شَیْ ءٍ مِنْهُ یَعْنِی وَلَدَ الزِّنَاءِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
          "9.  It  is  narrated  that  Imam  Muhammad  Baqir  (a.s.)  said, “There is no good in illegitimate children. Neither there is good in their skin nor in their hair, flesh, blood or any other thing.”"
        ]
      }
    },
